uchasSlotTable.name: uchasSlotTable
uchasSlotTable.description: A table that contains information about the slots in the chassis. For those slots that do not contain a physical module, the table will contain a conceptual row with the type of physical module set to 'uchasSlotEmpty'.

uchasSlotEntry.name: uchasSlotEntry
uchasSlotEntry.description: A list of information for each slot in the chassis. Conceptual rows may not be created or deleted with SNMP operations, but rather, the Proxy agent running in the Network Management Card will automatically create and delete rows as cards are inserted and removed.

uchasSlotIndex.name: uchasSlotIndex
uchasSlotIndex.description: The slot number for which this entry contains management information. NAC slots are numbered from 1 to 16. The Network Management Card (NMC) goes in slot 17. For simplicity's sake, the corresponding NIC slot numbers will be 21 through 37. Rows will not exist in this table for slots 18 through 20.

uchasSlotModuleType.name: uchasSlotModuleType
uchasSlotModuleType.description: The type of physical module contained in this slot of the chassis. A value of uchasSlotEmpty indicates an empty slot. A value of uchasSlotUnknown indicates that the type of module is unknown.

uchasSlotLastChange.name: uchasSlotLastChange
uchasSlotLastChange.description: The value of MIB-II's sysUpTime (in the agent supporting this chassis MIB) at which a module was last inserted or removed from this slot. If no module has been inserted or removed from this slot since the last time the network management card was re-initialized, then this object has a zero value.

uchasSlotModuleDescr.name: uchasSlotModuleDescr
uchasSlotModuleDescr.description: A textual description of the module plugged into the slot.

uchasSlotModuleVersion.name: uchasSlotModuleVersion
uchasSlotModuleVersion.description: A textual description of the version/revision level for this module's hardware.

uchasSlotModuleSerialNumber.name: uchasSlotModuleSerialNumber
uchasSlotModuleSerialNumber.description: The serial number of the module present in the slot. If the slot is empty, this value will be a zero length string.

uchasSlotModuleProductCode.name: uchasSlotModuleProductCode
uchasSlotModuleProductCode.description: The product code of the module present in the slot. For certain entries in the slot table the NMC will not be able to read product codes. In such cases the product code string will be NULL.

uchasSlotStatFeEna.name: uchasSlotStatFeEna
uchasSlotStatFeEna.description: This object can be read to determine what options have been enabled in the NACs. It uses individual bits to represent the enable status of the features which are NAC specific.

uchasSlotFeKey.name: uchasSlotFeKey
uchasSlotFeKey.description: This object sends the feature key to the appropriate NAC for enabling added cost features. When read, this object returns a null string.

uchasSlotNacConfig.name: uchasSlotNacConfig
uchasSlotNacConfig.description: This is a proprietary encoding of a module's view of the chassis NAC configuration as it is stored in the module. For modules not supporting chassis configuration storage, the values will be all 0.

uchasSlotSwitchSettings.name: uchasSlotSwitchSettings
uchasSlotSwitchSettings.description: This represents the DIP switch settings on the NAC. It is a bitmapped integer.

uchasSlotRamInstalled.name: uchasSlotRamInstalled
uchasSlotRamInstalled.description: This represents the amount of DRAM memory installed on the NAC in Kbytes.

uchasSlotFlashInstalled.name: uchasSlotFlashInstalled
uchasSlotFlashInstalled.description: This represents the amount of flash ROM memory installed on the NAC in Kbytes.

uchasEntityTable.name: uchasEntityTable
uchasEntityTable.description: A table that contains information about the 'logical' networking devices (entities) in this chassis.

uchasEntityEntry.name: uchasEntityEntry
uchasEntityEntry.description: Information concerning an entity in the chassis. Conceptual rows may not be created or deleted with SNMP operations, but rather, will be automatically created and deleted by the proxy agent running on the Network Management Card.

uchasEntityIndex.name: uchasEntityIndex
uchasEntityIndex.description: A unique index for the entity for which this entry contains information. For simplicity's sake, entity index values will be assigned according to the formula E=1000*S+I, where E is the entity index, S is the slot index, and I is the index of the entity on the specific card. For example, the third modem on a quad modem card that is in slot 5 has an entity index of 5003.

uchasEntityObjectID.name: uchasEntityObjectID
uchasEntityObjectID.description: The specific type of entity. The value of this object is analogous to MIB-II's sysObjectID. In particular, it has the same value as would be returned if the MIB view identified by uchasIpAddress and uchasCommunity, were queried for sysObjectID.

uchasEntityDescr.name: uchasEntityDescr
uchasEntityDescr.description: A textual description of the entity. The value of this object is analogous to MIB-II's sysDescr. In particular, it has the same value as would be returned if the MIB view identified by uchasIpAddress and uchasCommunity were queried for sysDescr.

uchasEntityVersion.name: uchasEntityVersion
uchasEntityVersion.description: A textual description of the version/revision level for this entity's software.

uchasEntityOperStatus.name: uchasEntityOperStatus
uchasEntityOperStatus.description: Provides operational status of the entity for which this row corresponds.

uchasEntityTimeStamp.name: uchasEntityTimeStamp
uchasEntityTimeStamp.description: The value of MIB-II's sysUpTime (in the NMC's proxy agent) at which this entity was last (re-)initialized.

uchasType.name: uchasType
uchasType.description: An authoritative identification of the type of chassis. This object provides an easy and unambiguaous means for determining what kind of box is being managed.

uchasDescr.name: uchasDescr
uchasDescr.description: A textual description of the specific chassis being managed.

uchasDisplayName.name: uchasDisplayName
uchasDisplayName.description: A four digit name given to the chassis. The name will be displayed on the alpha-numeric display on the front panel of the Network Management Card in the given chassis.

uchasPhysicalChanges.name: uchasPhysicalChanges
uchasPhysicalChanges.description: The number of physical changes that have occurred in the chassis since the agent was warm/cold started. This includes additions and removal of physical modules.

uchasFrontPanelLedStates.name: uchasFrontPanelLedStates
uchasFrontPanelLedStates.description: This object is a proprietarily encoded octet string that is used by USR's management console to retrieve the front panel LED states (attributes) from all of the devices installed in the chassis by getting a single object.

uchasFrontPanelLedColor.name: uchasFrontPanelLedColor
uchasFrontPanelLedColor.description: This object is a proprietary encoded octet string used to get the color of every LED from all the devices in the chassis.

uchasNicStates.name: uchasNicStates
uchasNicStates.description: This object is a proprietary encoded octet string used to get the status of every NIC in the chassis.

uchasPowerSupplyTable.name: uchasPowerSupplyTable
uchasPowerSupplyTable.description: A list of power supply entries, one for each power supply in the chassis. This table is a dense table, so rows appear for all possible power supplies that could be present in the given chassis.

uchasPowerSupplyEntry.name: uchasPowerSupplyEntry
uchasPowerSupplyEntry.description: There is one entry in the power supply table for each possible power supply in the chassis.

uchasPowerSupplyIndex.name: uchasPowerSupplyIndex
uchasPowerSupplyIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies a power supply.

uchasPowerSupplyDescr.name: uchasPowerSupplyDescr
uchasPowerSupplyDescr.description: A textual description of the power supply.

uchasPowerSupplyOperStatus.name: uchasPowerSupplyOperStatus
uchasPowerSupplyOperStatus.description: Actual status of the power supply represented by this entry in the power supply table.

uchasPowerSupplyFailures.name: uchasPowerSupplyFailures
uchasPowerSupplyFailures.description: The number of times that uchasPowerSupplyOperStatus has gone to bad(4).

uchasPowerSupplyOutTable.name: uchasPowerSupplyOutTable
uchasPowerSupplyOutTable.description: A list of power supply output entries, one for each output of each power supply in the chassis.

uchasPowerSupplyOutEntry.name: uchasPowerSupplyOutEntry
uchasPowerSupplyOutEntry.description: There is one row in this table for each power supply output for each power supply in the chassis.

uchasPowerSupplyOutPSIndex.name: uchasPowerSupplyOutPSIndex
uchasPowerSupplyOutPSIndex.description: An index which specifies the power supply to which this output relates. The value of this index corresponds directly to values of the index for the power supply table.

uchasPowerSupplyOutIndex.name: uchasPowerSupplyOutIndex
uchasPowerSupplyOutIndex.description: An index that, together with uchasPowerSupplyOutPSIndex, uniquely defines an output for the specified power supply.

uchasPowerSupplyOutStatus.name: uchasPowerSupplyOutStatus
uchasPowerSupplyOutStatus.description: Actual status of the supply output. One of unknown(1), warning(2), or good(3).

uchasPowerSupplyOutNominalVolt.name: uchasPowerSupplyOutNominalVolt
uchasPowerSupplyOutNominalVolt.description: In hundredths of a volt, the voltage the output is supposed to supply, such as -5V, which would be represented by the value -500, or +12V, which would correspond to a value of +1200.

uchasPowerSupplyOutOfferedVolt.name: uchasPowerSupplyOutOfferedVolt
uchasPowerSupplyOutOfferedVolt.description: In hundredths of a volt, the voltage actually offered by the output. If uchasPowerSupplyOutStatus is good(4), the value 0 means offered voltage is not available.

uchasPowerSupplyOutWarnings.name: uchasPowerSupplyOutWarnings
uchasPowerSupplyOutWarnings.description: The number of times uchasPowerSupplyOutputStatus has gone to warning(3).

uchasEnvironTable.name: uchasEnvironTable
uchasEnvironTable.description: A list of environmental entries, one for each environmental sensor in the chassis.

uchasEnvironEntry.name: uchasEnvironEntry
uchasEnvironEntry.description: Values for an environmental sensor in the chassis.

uchasEnvironIndex.name: uchasEnvironIndex
uchasEnvironIndex.description: A index that uniquely identifies an environmental sensor.

uchasEnvironSensor.name: uchasEnvironSensor
uchasEnvironSensor.description: The identification of the type of environmental sensor to which this entry applies.

uchasEnvironStatus.name: uchasEnvironStatus
uchasEnvironStatus.description: Actual status indicated by the sensor.

uchasEnvironWarnings.name: uchasEnvironWarnings
uchasEnvironWarnings.description: The number of times uchasEnvironStatus has gone to warning(3).

uchasEnvironFailures.name: uchasEnvironFailures
uchasEnvironFailures.description: The number of times uchasEnvironStatus has gone to bad(2).

uchasCmdTable.name: uchasCmdTable
uchasCmdTable.description: The Chassis Command table contains an entry for each of the NIC and NAC slots in the chassis. It provides a means through which to take specific actions on one or more devices in the chassis at a card level. Device specific commands are not included here, but rather in the specific MIB used to manage the device.

uchasCmdEntry.name: uchasCmdEntry
uchasCmdEntry.description: There is one entry in this table for each row in uchasSlotTable.

uchasCmdSlotIndex.name: uchasCmdSlotIndex
uchasCmdSlotIndex.description: This index uniquely identifies the slot to which the command being written is to take place. Values of uchasCmdSlotIndex correspond to values used to index uchasSlotTable.

uchasCmdMgtStationId.name: uchasCmdMgtStationId
uchasCmdMgtStationId.description: This object is a generic read-write variable that a Management Station (MS) can use to guarantee that the results from a given command are the results of a command issued by that specific MS. Each MS must SET a unique value to this object when doing commands and GET the value of this object together with uchasCmdReqId and uchasCmdResult to detect interference from other MSs.

uchasCmdReqId.name: uchasCmdReqId
uchasCmdReqId.description: Ths object contains the value of the request-id field in the SNMP PDU which invoked the current or most recent command on the device in the specified slot of the chassis. If the request-id is unknown or undefined, this value contains the value zero.

uchasCmdFunction.name: uchasCmdFunction
uchasCmdFunction.description: A control variable used to start and stop operator-initiated commands. A command is initiated by setting this object to a value other than noCommand(1). When the value noCommand(1) is written to this object, no action is taken, unless a command is in progress, in which case the command is aborted.

uchasCmdForce.name: uchasCmdForce
uchasCmdForce.description: In some cases, the devices in the chassis may be in a state such that certain commands could adversely affect connections or other device specific operations. In such cases, a command with uchasCmdForce set to noForce will result in a warning. If the operator elects to ignore such warnings, uchasCmdForce can be set to force in the command request and the command will be carried out regardless of its potentially hazzardous effects.

uchasCmdParam.name: uchasCmdParam
uchasCmdParam.description: This object contains parameters that are specific to the particular command being issued. In some cases, there will be no additional parameters required.

uchasCmdResult.name: uchasCmdResult
uchasCmdResult.description: This object contains the result of the most recently requested test, or the value none(1) if not commands have been requested since the last reset. Note that this facility provides no provision for saving the results of one command when starting another, as could be required if used by multiple managers concurrently.

uchasCmdCode.name: uchasCmdCode
uchasCmdCode.description: The value of this object upon command completion indicates a further description of what went wrong if the command was unsuccessful. This object is also used as an indication of the in progress status of the software download command.

uchasModuleInsertedTrapEna.name: uchasModuleInsertedTrapEna
uchasModuleInsertedTrapEna.description: Enables the generation of a trap when a card is inserted into the chassis. This parameter is effective across all slots in the chassis.

uchasModuleRemovedTrapEna.name: uchasModuleRemovedTrapEna
uchasModuleRemovedTrapEna.description: Enables the generation of a trap when a card is removed from the chassis. This parameter is effective across all slots in the chassis.

uchasPSUWarningTrapEna.name: uchasPSUWarningTrapEna
uchasPSUWarningTrapEna.description: Enables the generation of a trap when a power supply enters a warning state, such as one or more output voltages being out of range. This parameter is effective across all PSUs in the chassis.

uchasPSUFailureTrapEna.name: uchasPSUFailureTrapEna
uchasPSUFailureTrapEna.description: Enables the generation of a trap when a power supply fails and has been automatically shut down due to overvoltage, overcurrent, etc. This parameter is effective across all PSUs in the chassis.

uchasTempWarningTrapEna.name: uchasTempWarningTrapEna
uchasTempWarningTrapEna.description: Enables the generation of a trap when the temperature in the chassis, as detected by the NMC, becomes excessive.

uchasFanFailureTrapEna.name: uchasFanFailureTrapEna
uchasFanFailureTrapEna.description: Enables the generation of a trap when the fan in the chassis is not rotating with sufficient speed to cool the power supplies.

uchasEntityWatchdogTrapEna.name: uchasEntityWatchdogTrapEna
uchasEntityWatchdogTrapEna.description: Enables the generation of a trap when a logical networking entity in the chassis undergoes a watchdog timeout event, indicating software failure.

uchasEntityMgtBusFailTrapEna.name: uchasEntityMgtBusFailTrapEna
uchasEntityMgtBusFailTrapEna.description: Enables the generation of a trap when the SNMP proxy agent in the NMC is unable to communicate properly with a logical networking entity in the chassis.

uchasArPsuVoltOutOfRange.name: uchasArPsuVoltOutOfRange
uchasArPsuVoltOutOfRange.description: This script is triggered when the NMC detects that voltage levels, for at least one power supply on the mid plane, are outside the normal operating range.

uchasArPsuFailed.name: uchasArPsuFailed
uchasArPsuFailed.description: This script is triggered when the NMC detects an over-voltage or over-current condition present in the PSU.

uchasArFanFailed.name: uchasArFanFailed
uchasArFanFailed.description: This script is triggered when the fan speed becomes dangerously slow as to risk damage to inadequate cooling of the chassis.

uchasArHubTempOutOfRange.name: uchasArHubTempOutOfRange
uchasArHubTempOutOfRange.description: This script is triggered when the chassis temperature is outside the specified normal operating range.

uchasArTimer1.name: uchasArTimer1
uchasArTimer1.description: This script is triggered when the first general purpose timer expires.

uchasArTimer2.name: uchasArTimer2
uchasArTimer2.description: This script is triggered when the second general purpose timer expires.

uchasArTimer3.name: uchasArTimer3
uchasArTimer3.description: This script is triggered when the third general purpose timer expires.

uchasArTimer4.name: uchasArTimer4
uchasArTimer4.description: This script is triggered when the fourth general purpose timer expires.

uchasArSlotTable.name: uchasArSlotTable
uchasArSlotTable.description: A table that contains auto response scripts, in the chassis, that act on a particular slot.

uchasArSlotEntry.name: uchasArSlotEntry
uchasArSlotEntry.description: A list of auto response scripts, in the chassis, that act on a slot.

uchasArSlotIndex.name: uchasArSlotIndex
uchasArSlotIndex.description: The slot number for which this entry contains an auto response script. NAC slots are numbered from 1 to 16. The Network Management Card (NMC) goes into slot 17. To keep things simple, the corresponding NIC slot numbers are from 21 to 37. Rows for slots 18 to 20 do not exist.

uchasArModuleInserted.name: uchasArModuleInserted
uchasArModuleInserted.description: This script is triggered when a module is inserted in the chassis.

uchasArModuleReinit.name: uchasArModuleReinit
uchasArModuleReinit.description: This script is triggered when the following occur: chassis power transitions from off to on; a module is inserted in the chassis; software download has just been completed to a module; a module is restored to service; or a module is reset (hardware).

uchasArModuleRemoved.name: uchasArModuleRemoved
uchasArModuleRemoved.description: This script is triggered when a module is physically removed from the chassis.

uchasArModuleNonoper.name: uchasArModuleNonoper
uchasArModuleNonoper.description: This script is triggered when the following occur: software download to a module has just been started; a module is removed from service; or a module has failed (i.e. all entities on that module have failed).

uchasArModuleWatchdog.name: uchasArModuleWatchdog
uchasArModuleWatchdog.description: This script is triggered when one or more module entities experience a watchdog time-out.

uchasArTimerTable.name: uchasArTimerTable
uchasArTimerTable.description: A table that contains general purpose global timer parameters. These timers act on an entire chassis.

uchasArTimerEntry.name: uchasArTimerEntry
uchasArTimerEntry.description: A list of parameters for general purpose global timers.

uchasArTimerIndex.name: uchasArTimerIndex
uchasArTimerIndex.description: The number of general purpose global timers.

uchasArTimerEna.name: uchasArTimerEna
uchasArTimerEna.description: Enable or disable the specified global timer.

uchasArTimerStartDate.name: uchasArTimerStartDate
uchasArTimerStartDate.description: This object determines the date on which the timer becomes active. This date is compared against the system date, time and time zone defined in management entity. Default=01/01/95

uchasArTimerStartTime.name: uchasArTimerStartTime
uchasArTimerStartTime.description: This object determines the time on which the timer becomes active. This time is compared against the system date, time and time zone defined in management entity. Default=00:00:00

uchasArTimerStopDate.name: uchasArTimerStopDate
uchasArTimerStopDate.description: This object specifies the date on which this timer becomes passive. This date is compared against the system date, time and time zone defined in management entity. The timer will not be active if the timer stop date and time is less than system date and time. Default = 01/01/95

uchasArTimerStopTime.name: uchasArTimerStopTime
uchasArTimerStopTime.description: This object specifies the time on which this timer becomes passive. This time is compared against the system date, time and time zone defined in management entity. The timer will not be active if the timer stop date and time is less than system date and time. Default = 00:00:00

uchasArTimerInterval.name: uchasArTimerInterval
uchasArTimerInterval.description: The interval in seconds between each timer firing. The firings will happen at each interval after the timer starts until the date/time specified if the following 2 conditions are met. First, TimerInterval must be less than or equal to the timer active period. Second, The start date/time is less than the stop date/time. The timer will fire only once at stop date/time if a zero value has been assigned to this object. Default = 0. Max 259000 sec = 30 days.

uchasArTimerState.name: uchasArTimerState
uchasArTimerState.description: This object indicates the current state of the global timer.

uchasArTimerTriggers.name: uchasArTimerTriggers
uchasArTimerTriggers.description: This object indicates the number of times that a global timer has triggered since the last system boot time.
